DDL(Data Definitoin Langauge)
- Database: CREATE, DROP
- Schema: CREATE
- Table: CREATE TABLE, ALTER TABLE, DROP TABLE
- Data Types
    - Date, Time: DATE, TIME, DATETIME
- Constraints: PRIMARY KEY, FOREIGN KEY, UNIQUE, CHECK, DEFAULT
- Index

DCL(Data Control Language)
- User Management: Privilege, Role, CREATE USER, GRANT, REVOKE, DROP USER
- Security
- SSL

DML(Data Manipulation Language)
- Query: INSERT, SELECT, UPDATE, DELETE
- Join: INNER JOIN, LEFT JOIN, RIGHT JOIN, FULL JOIN
- Order By, Group By
- Limit, Offset
- Count
- Prepared Statement

TCL(Transaction Contol Language)
- Transaction: START TRANSACTION, COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT

Object
- Views
- Triggers
- Stored Procedures
- Functions

Engine
- MySQL Engine
- InnoDB
- MyISAM

Integrity
- Data Integrity
- Reference Integrity

Data 
- Concurrent Control/Lock
- Backup & Recovery: mysqldump
- Replication
- Partitioning

High Availability
- Clustering

Performance Tuning
- Execution Plan
- Optimizer

OTHERS
- Connection Management
- Normalization
- SQL Injection
- Reserved Words


